  "SubGoals": [],
  "Description": "The HandleBuildGoalFailure goal is designed to manage errors that occur during a build process. It checks the status code of the error and takes appropriate actions based on its value. If the status code is 402 or greater than or equal to 500, it throws the error. It also appends the error to the goal's error list and checks if the retry count exceeds 3, in which case it throws the error again. If the retry count is 3 or less, it logs a retry message and calls the BuildGoal function.",
  "Visibility": 0,
  "GoalFileName": "BuildGoal.goal",
